duck: Completion (oil and gas wells) - In petroleum production, completion is the process of making a well ready for production.
Completion (American football) - A completion is a term used in American football when a receiver successfully catches a pass.

Autocomplete - Autocomplete is a feature provided by many web browsers, e-mail programs, search engine interfaces, source code editors, database query tools, word processors, and command line interpreters.
Completeness - In general, an object is complete if nothing needs to be added to it.
completion definition: the act or process of completing.
one stage of Conveyancing, transfer of the title of property from one person to another
